HEADWORD: Withe-rod
<hw>Withe"-rod`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A North American shrub (<spn>Viburnum nudum</spn>) whose tough
osierlike shoots are sometimes used for binding sheaves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

